Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Italian Family 3: Studio discussion
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01mdgpk
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 10 Sep 2012
What has cause the Italian family to decline so fast? What are the prospects for encouraging Italians to start having more children? Laurie is joined in the studio by three experts in order to discuss his explorations of the family in Italy. Geoff Andrews, David Gilmour and Annalisa Piras give their views on what has caused the Italian crisis and what hopes there are for the future. Producer: Charlie Taylor. Show less